  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dbd\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dba \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dab\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dbd \u0d85\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0dc5\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The creators of the National Fuel License are revealed",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Power and Energy Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera has made a revelation on his Twitter account about the parties who created the National Fuel Licensing System (QR).",
        "Thus, the Minister said that the Information Technology Agency, Dialog Institute and Millennium Information Technology Company created this fuel license system on behalf of the Ministry of Power and Energy.",
        "Earlier, the minister had mentioned that the Information Technology Agency and two other private organizations introduced this national fuel license system, but the two private companies did not want to reveal their names.",
        "The Minister further said that the National Fuel Permit System was introduced free of cost and thanks to all the stakeholders and volunteers who supported it."
      ],
